WEBVTT

00:02.473 --> 00:05.476
[ "ME AND BABY BROTHER"
 PLAYING ]

00:18.319 --> 00:21.592
♫ ME AND BABY BROTHER ♫

00:21.592 --> 00:24.325
♫ USED TO RUN TOGETHER ♫

00:24.325 --> 00:25.656
HEY, GEORGE!

00:25.656 --> 00:28.499
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE
 ON LADIES NIGHT?

00:28.499 --> 00:31.332
JUST NEEDED
 SOME PEACE AND QUIET.

00:31.332 --> 00:32.603
WHAT´S THAT?

00:32.603 --> 00:35.336
MY DAD FOUND OUT
 I NEEDED MONEY,

00:35.336 --> 00:37.508
SO HE SENT ME A CHECK
 FOR $20,000.

00:37.508 --> 00:38.739
THAT´S GREAT.

00:38.739 --> 00:40.411
NOW YOU CAN PAY BACK
 ANGIE´S COMPANY

00:40.411 --> 00:42.543
FOR ALL THAT STUFF
 THAT BURNED UP IN THE GARAGE.

00:42.543 --> 00:44.075
YEAH, IF I DON´T MIND
 TAKING MONEY

00:44.075 --> 00:46.117
FROM A GUY WHO ABANDONED
 ME AND MY MOM.

00:46.117 --> 00:49.080
HEY, I´LL TELL YOU WHAT THEY SAY
 ON "TEXAS JUSTICE."

00:49.080 --> 00:51.252
JUDGE LARRY WOULD SAY,
 "THE MONEY´S YOURS!

00:51.252 --> 00:53.484
THAT´S THE DECISION
 OF THE COURT! BAM!"

00:53.484 --> 00:57.228
KEEP IT UP, AND YOU´LL
 NEVER SCORE WITH ANY
 WOMAN IN THIS BAR.

00:57.228 --> 00:58.329
BAM!

00:58.329 --> 00:59.760
HEY, GOOD LOOKIN´.

00:59.760 --> 01:03.334
ANGIE, I TOLD YOU
 I NEEDED TO BE ALONE.

01:03.334 --> 01:07.268
HEY, ERNIE, DID YOU SEE THAT
 BRUNETTE OVER BY THE JUKEBOX?

01:07.268 --> 01:08.539
SHE WAS CHECKIN´ YOU OUT.

01:08.539 --> 01:10.101
REALLY?
 HOW DO I LOOK?

01:10.101 --> 01:11.472
NO, DON´T TELL ME.

01:11.472 --> 01:13.244
I WANT TO FEEL CONFIDENT
 WHEN I GO OVER THERE.

01:13.244 --> 01:16.507
YOU GOT ABOUT 10 SECONDS BEFORE
 HE FIGURES OUT YOU WERE LYING.

01:16.507 --> 01:18.309
I´M GOING WITH YOU
 TO SEE YOUR DAD.

01:18.309 --> 01:19.410
NO.

01:19.410 --> 01:21.382
WHICH BRUNETTE?
 THE OTHER ONE.

01:21.382 --> 01:23.814
BUT I WANT TO HELP YOU.

01:23.814 --> 01:26.587
I NEED TO BE ALONE SO I CAN
 THINK ABOUT THIS ON THE DRIVE.

01:26.587 --> 01:29.520
YOU SAID TO CONSIDER TAKING THE
 CHECK BECAUSE WE NEED THE MONEY.

01:29.520 --> 01:31.622
I KNOW THAT,
 BUT EVERYTHING´S DIFFERENT NOW.

01:31.622 --> 01:34.094
I MEAN, I DIDN´T WANT TO MEET
 MY DAD FOR THE FIRST TIME

01:34.094 --> 01:35.566
COMING TO HIM FOR MONEY.

01:35.566 --> 01:38.869
I WON´T TALK, I PROMISE.
 I JUST WANT TO BE THERE FOR YOU.

01:38.869 --> 01:40.371
NO.

01:40.371 --> 01:42.133
GEORGE, THERE´S
 THE FIGHTS THAT I WIN,

01:42.133 --> 01:43.834
AND THERE´S THE FIGHTS
 THAT I LET YOU WIN.

01:43.834 --> 01:46.237
THIS IS ONE OF THE FIGHTS
 THAT I WIN. I´M GOING.

01:47.508 --> 01:50.311
♫ BABY BROTHER ♫

01:50.311 --> 01:52.513
IS THIS THE ONE
 YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT, ANGIE?

01:52.513 --> 01:54.245
´CAUSE IT´S NOT FUNNY.

01:54.245 --> 01:58.219
I´M SORRY. I JUST NEEDED
 TO TALK TO MY HUSBAND ALONE.

01:58.219 --> 02:00.891
♫ YOU´RE MY BABY BROTHER ♫

02:00.891 --> 02:02.253
♫ AY-YI-YI ♫

02:02.253 --> 02:03.754
I WOULDN´T LET HIM GO.

02:03.754 --> 02:07.828
AT LEAST YOU KNOW WHAT
 YOU´RE GETTING WITH THOSE PANTS.

02:11.432 --> 02:13.604
♫ LOVE MY BABY BROTHER ♫

02:13.604 --> 02:15.536
♫ YOU BET I ♫

02:15.536 --> 02:17.538
♫ LOVE MY BABY BROTHER ♫

02:17.538 --> 02:19.710
♫ AAAAHHHH ♫

02:19.710 --> 02:22.543
CARMEN, GET YOUR BUTT
 OFF THE COUNTER.

02:22.543 --> 02:23.744
WE EAT THERE!

02:23.744 --> 02:26.517
NO, DAD,
 WE EAT SUR LA TABLE.

02:26.517 --> 02:27.818
RESPECTEZ UN PèRE.

02:27.818 --> 02:29.280
MAIS REGARDEZ LE FOU!

02:29.280 --> 02:32.553
IL NE SAIT PAS
 LE FRANAIS.

02:32.553 --> 02:34.585
YOU KNOW, YOU TWO CAN TALK
 IN ANY LANGUAGE,

02:34.585 --> 02:37.288
BUT IT ALL SOUNDS LIKE --
 [ IMITATES CHICKEN CLUCKING ]

02:41.732 --> 02:44.195
BENNY, I´M GLAD YOU´RE HERE.

02:44.195 --> 02:46.397
HEY, THAT SOUNDS STRANGE,
 DOESN´T IT?

02:46.397 --> 02:48.539
I´M GOING WITH GEORGE TOMORROW
 TO MEET HIS DAD IN PHOENIX.

02:48.539 --> 02:50.941
WE NEED YOU TO WATCH THE KIDS
 FOR A DAY.

02:50.941 --> 02:53.374
HELL, NO!
 IF HE´S GOING, I´M GOING.

02:53.374 --> 02:56.407
WHY? I THOUGHT YOU NEVER WANTED
 TO SEE HIM AGAIN.

02:56.407 --> 02:57.808
I DON´T.

02:57.808 --> 02:59.910
BUT I DON´T WANT HIM TELLING YOU
 A BUNCH OF LIES

02:59.910 --> 03:01.352
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED
 BETWEEN US.

03:01.352 --> 03:03.183
MOM, THERE´S NOTHING
 HE CAN SAY

03:03.183 --> 03:05.516
THAT CAN CHANGE THE WAY
 I FEEL ABOUT YOU.

03:05.516 --> 03:07.318
THANK YOU.

03:07.318 --> 03:09.189
THAT´S NOT A GOOD THING.

03:09.189 --> 03:11.322
I´M GOING!

03:11.322 --> 03:12.693
WELL, IF BENNY´S GOING,

03:12.693 --> 03:14.895
THEN THE KIDS ARE GONNA
 HAVE TO COME, TOO.

03:14.895 --> 03:17.197
OH, I CAN´T GO.

03:17.197 --> 03:18.669
OLIVIA AND I HAVE A SCIENCE
 PROJECT DUE MONDAY,

03:18.669 --> 03:20.731
AND I WAS GONNA STAY OVER
 HER PLACE TOMORROW NIGHT.

03:20.731 --> 03:21.732
FINE.

03:21.732 --> 03:23.574
THEN IT´S JUST YOU, MAX.

03:23.574 --> 03:26.877
BUT WHO´S GOING TO WATCH
 MR. NEEDLES?

03:26.877 --> 03:28.909
WELL, HE CAN COME, TOO.

03:28.909 --> 03:30.381
ANYONE ELSE, ANGIE?

03:30.381 --> 03:32.983
MAYBE YOUR PARENTS
 WOULD LIKE TO SEE PHOENIX.

03:32.983 --> 03:35.386
´CAUSE NOW
 MY PAINFUL PERSONAL JOURNEY

03:35.386 --> 03:37.588
HAS TURNED INTO
 A FAMILY VACATION.

03:37.588 --> 03:39.450
OH, LET´S NOT FORGET
 THE CAMERA.

03:39.450 --> 03:41.692
HERE´S ME WEEPING
 AT THE GRAND CANYON.

03:41.692 --> 03:43.554
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

03:43.554 --> 03:45.356
WOULDN´T IT BE BETTER
 TO DEAL WITH THIS

03:45.356 --> 03:47.628
SURROUNDED BY ALL THE PEOPLE
 THAT LOVE AND SUPPORT YOU?

03:47.628 --> 03:49.630
BEFORE I MARRIED YOU,
 MY LIFE WAS JUST FINE

03:49.630 --> 03:51.502
WITHOUT LOVE AND SUPPORT.
 RIGHT, MOM?

03:51.502 --> 03:54.765
I HARDLY KNEW YOU WERE THERE.

04:06.777 --> 04:07.978
SO...[CHUCKLES]

04:07.978 --> 04:10.621
WHAT BRINGS YOU HERE
 ON LADIES NIGHT?

04:10.621 --> 04:13.384
YOU´VE BEEN SITTING THERE
 LOOKING AT ME FOR 3 HOURS,

04:13.384 --> 04:15.356
AND THAT´S
 WHAT YOU CAME UP WITH?

04:17.788 --> 04:19.259
LOOK, UM...

04:19.259 --> 04:21.791
I-I´M NOT VERY GOOD AT THIS.

04:21.791 --> 04:26.266
IF YOU WENT OUT WITH ME, YOU´D
 SEE I´M A REALLY NICE PERSON.

04:26.266 --> 04:27.798
WHAT ELSE YOU GOT?

04:30.401 --> 04:32.403
SEE YA.
 DRIVE SAFE.

04:38.979 --> 04:40.050
HEY.

04:40.050 --> 04:41.312
YEAH?

04:41.312 --> 04:42.683
ALL RIGHT, COME ON.

04:46.387 --> 04:48.689
[ INTRO TO "LOW RIDER" PLAYS ]

05:09.440 --> 05:14.615
♫ ALL MY FRIENDS
 KNOW THE LOW RIDER ♫

05:16.347 --> 05:21.792
♫ THE LOW RIDER
 IS A LITTLE HIGHER ♫

05:44.945 --> 05:47.347
[ UPBEAT LATIN MUSIC PLAYS ]

05:50.751 --> 05:53.384
[ MID-TEMPO LATIN MUSIC PLAYS ]

05:55.786 --> 05:58.829
[ TEX-MEX MUSIC PLAYS ]

05:58.829 --> 06:01.732
IT´S NICE TO BE THE NATION´S
 LARGEST MINORITY,

06:01.732 --> 06:04.965
BUT COULDN´T WE LEAVE ON DAMNED
 SOUL STATION IN THE DESERT?

06:04.965 --> 06:08.138
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

06:08.138 --> 06:11.772
[ MID-TEMPO POP MUSIC PLAYS ]

06:11.772 --> 06:13.774
[ SNORES ]

06:19.850 --> 06:22.513
[ GRUNTING ]

06:23.554 --> 06:26.857
OKAY, BENNY, ONE MORE PUSH!

06:26.857 --> 06:27.888
MM-HMM.

06:27.888 --> 06:29.820
HERE COMES THE HEAD.

06:29.820 --> 06:31.562
OH, DAMN YOU, MANNY!

06:31.562 --> 06:34.965
TAKE A BEDPAN
 AND KNOCK ME UNCONSCIOUS!

06:34.965 --> 06:36.827
IT´S HERE!

06:36.827 --> 06:39.800
[ CRYING ]

06:39.800 --> 06:41.902
OH, MY GOD.

06:41.902 --> 06:44.505
HE´S -- HE´S BEAUTIFUL.

06:44.505 --> 06:47.177
[ CRYING CONTINUES ]

06:47.177 --> 06:50.641
I´M NOT NURSING THAT THING!

06:52.182 --> 06:55.846
AAAAAAHHH!

06:55.846 --> 06:58.489
[ CRYING CONTINUES ]

06:58.489 --> 07:01.852
[ BARKING ]

07:01.852 --> 07:03.994
[ BARKING ]

07:03.994 --> 07:06.997
THERE´S SOMETHING WRONG
 WITH MR. NEEDLES.

07:06.997 --> 07:08.459
LET ME SEE HIM, HONEY.

07:11.832 --> 07:13.133
HE LOOKS OKAY.

07:13.133 --> 07:14.635
AND HE´S NOT HUNGRY,
 EITHER.

07:14.635 --> 07:15.135
I FED HIM SOME LICORICE
 AND CHEESE PUFFS.

07:15.135 --> 07:18.469
[ FARTS ]

07:18.469 --> 07:19.740
OHH! OHH!
 OHH! OHH!

07:19.740 --> 07:21.472
PASS HIM BACK
 BEFORE HE BLOWS.

07:21.472 --> 07:22.673
OHH! OH-OH!

07:22.673 --> 07:25.846
WE´LL STOP
 AT THE NEXT REST AREA.

07:25.846 --> 07:27.778
OHH! OHH!
 OHH! OHH!

07:27.778 --> 07:31.752
OKAY, THAT LAST ONE
 WAS NOT THE DOG.

07:40.891 --> 07:42.032
GEORGE...

07:42.032 --> 07:43.794
WHAT?

07:43.794 --> 07:47.167
HAVE YOU DECIDED WHETHER OR NOT
 YOU´RE GONNA FORGIVE YOUR DAD?

07:47.167 --> 07:50.100
HOW CAN I DECIDE ANYTHING?
 I HAVEN´T HAD TIME TO THINK.

07:50.100 --> 07:51.872
I DON´T KNOW WHAT I´M GONNA DO.

07:51.872 --> 07:53.173
MAGIC 8-BALL...

07:53.173 --> 07:55.946
SHOULD MY DAD FORGIVE HIS DAD
 OR NOT?

07:57.848 --> 08:00.110
"REPLY HAZY.
 TRY AGAIN."

08:00.110 --> 08:01.812
MAGIC 8-BALL...

08:01.812 --> 08:03.784
ASK IT SOMETHING FOR ME, MAX.

08:03.784 --> 08:08.659
MAGIC 8-BALL, SHOULD MAX STOP
 ASKING ME QUESTIONS?

08:08.659 --> 08:09.920
"IT IS CERTAIN."

08:09.920 --> 08:11.662
DO IT, MAX...

08:11.662 --> 08:15.065
OR RISK THE CURSE OF THOSE
 WHO DEFY THE MAGIC 8-BALL.

08:17.167 --> 08:19.129
Magic 8-Ball...

08:19.129 --> 08:20.601
should I defy you?

08:20.601 --> 08:22.272
PUT IT AWAY!

08:25.606 --> 08:27.708
DAD, PICK A COLOR.
 WHAT?

08:27.708 --> 08:30.711
OH, A COOTIE CATCHER.
 I REMEMBER THOSE.

08:30.711 --> 08:32.582
LET ME SEE THAT, MAX.

08:34.885 --> 08:35.846
THOSE WERE FUN.

08:35.846 --> 08:36.947
DAD!

08:36.947 --> 08:39.720
MAX, PUT YOUR SEATBELT
 BACK ON.

08:39.720 --> 08:42.823
WHEN ARE WE GONNA PULL OVER?
 I NEED A SMOKE.

08:42.823 --> 08:45.225
I TOLD YOU
 TO BRING YOUR GUM.

08:45.225 --> 08:46.557
I CHEWED IT ALL.

08:50.300 --> 08:54.204
OKAY, HONEY, ONE MORE TIME.

08:54.204 --> 08:56.136
ONE CIGARETTE...

08:56.136 --> 08:57.968
TWO CIGARETTES...

08:59.009 --> 09:00.571
A-POOP!

09:00.571 --> 09:03.574
THREE CIGARETTES!

09:03.574 --> 09:06.246
SIX-PACK?

09:06.246 --> 09:09.079
OH, NO,
 THAT WAS YESTERDAY´S LESSON.

09:09.079 --> 09:10.851
COME ON, YOU CAN DO IT.

09:10.851 --> 09:13.854
CIGARETTE.

09:13.854 --> 09:14.985
VERY GOOD!

09:16.727 --> 09:19.259
IT´S 2:00 IN THE MORNING.
 WHAT´S THE KID STILL DOING UP?

09:19.259 --> 09:21.892
AND WHAT THE HELL IS HE DOING
 AROUND CIGARETTES?

09:23.293 --> 09:26.236
HE WANTED TO SAY GOOD NIGHT TO
 HIS DADDY, BUT HE WASN´T HOME.

09:26.236 --> 09:27.998
I STOPPED FOR A BEER
 AFTER WORK.

09:27.998 --> 09:30.100
YOU KNOW WHAT I DID
 AFTER WORK, MANNY?

09:30.100 --> 09:32.643
I TOOK THE BUS AND PICKED UP
 GEORGE FROM MY MOM´S.

09:32.643 --> 09:34.705
THEN WE CAME HOME
 AND WAITED FOR YOU.

09:34.705 --> 09:37.748
WE GOT KINDA BORED,
 SO I TAUGHT GEORGE A NEW WORD.

09:37.748 --> 09:39.349
WHAT WAS THAT NEW WORD,
 HONEY?

09:39.349 --> 09:42.182
CHEATER?

09:43.884 --> 09:45.315
ONE TIME, BENNY.

09:45.315 --> 09:47.788
NOW EVERY TIME I´M LATE,
 YOU THINK I´M WITH A WOMAN.

09:47.788 --> 09:50.120
IT´S BEEN 6 HOURS, MANNY.

09:50.120 --> 09:51.722
YOU´RE JUST PARANOID

09:51.722 --> 09:53.223
BECAUSE THE LOPEZ MEN
 ARE SO GOOD-LOOKING, HUH?

09:53.223 --> 09:56.667
IF YOU COULD JUST
 GROW INTO THAT HEAD.

09:56.667 --> 09:57.928
MAN, ONE OF THESE DAYS,

09:57.928 --> 09:59.900
THAT THING IS JUST GONNA SNAP
 RIGHT OFF.

09:59.900 --> 10:01.772
YEAH, KEEP RUNNING AROUND,

10:01.772 --> 10:03.734
ONE OF THESE DAYS SOMETHING OF
 YOURS IS GONNA SNAP RIGHT OFF.

10:03.734 --> 10:04.705
DROP IT, BENNY!

10:04.705 --> 10:06.076
START COMING HOME ON TIME!

10:06.076 --> 10:07.307
I WOULD IF I DIDN´T HAVE TO
 COME HOME TO YOU!

10:07.307 --> 10:08.779
SCREW YOU!

10:08.779 --> 10:12.683
I´M OUT OF HERE.
 I´M GETTING SOME SMOKES.

10:12.683 --> 10:14.985
YOU GOT SMOKES RIGHT HERE.

10:14.985 --> 10:16.016
PICK ANOTHER LIE.

10:16.016 --> 10:18.849
ILL STICK TO MY FIRST ONE!

10:18.849 --> 10:21.051
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

10:36.036 --> 10:39.740
I THINK WE JUST FLOODED
 A PRAIRIE DOG´S HOUSE.

10:39.740 --> 10:40.941
LET´S GET OUT OF HERE.

10:40.941 --> 10:42.642
LISTEN...

10:42.642 --> 10:46.176
NOW THAT WE´RE ALONE, I GOT
 SOMETHING I WANT TO GIVE YOU.

10:46.176 --> 10:47.878
WHAT IS IT?

10:47.878 --> 10:51.251
IT´S A LETTER YOUR FATHER WROTE
 YOU WHEN YOU WERE 4.

10:51.251 --> 10:52.422
YEAH.

10:52.422 --> 10:54.955
WHY DIDN´T YOU
 EVER GIVE IT TO ME?

10:54.955 --> 10:56.186
I THINK I JUST DID.

10:56.186 --> 10:58.729
I´M TALKING ABOUT
 32 YEARS AGO.

10:58.729 --> 11:02.032
IT CAME 2 YEARS AFTER HE LEFT.
 YOU WERE GETTING ALONG FINE.

11:02.032 --> 11:04.134
OF COURSE I WAS!
 YOU TOLD ME HE WAS DEAD!

11:04.134 --> 11:06.666
OKAY. IF THIS IS GONNA BE
 A WITCH-HUNT...

11:06.666 --> 11:08.198
STOP IT.

11:14.674 --> 11:16.006
"DEAR GEORGE,

11:16.006 --> 11:19.379
"YOU MAY BE TOO YOUNG
 TO UNDERSTAND,

11:19.379 --> 11:23.083
"BUT YOU´RE BETTER OFF
 WITHOUT ME.

11:23.083 --> 11:24.885
"JUST REMEMBER --

11:24.885 --> 11:29.790
"I´M LEAVING YOUR MOTHER.
 I´M NOT LEAVING YOU.

11:29.790 --> 11:31.291
LOVE, DAD."

11:31.291 --> 11:33.263
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THIS WOULD HAVE
 MEANT TO ME AS A KID?

11:33.263 --> 11:34.995
WHAT KIND OF MOTHER ARE YOU?!

11:34.995 --> 11:38.999
OH, YEAH, I RAISE YOU FOR 18
 YEARS. HE WRITES YOU ONE LETTER.

11:38.999 --> 11:40.230
IT´S A TIE.

11:40.230 --> 11:41.732
I´M TIRED OF THIS.

11:41.732 --> 11:44.204
YOU TOLD ME HE NEVER TRIED
 TO CONTACT ME,

11:44.204 --> 11:46.807
THAT HE WAS DEAD,
 THAT HE NEVER HELD ME,

11:46.807 --> 11:49.239
THAT EVERYBODY PAYS RENT
 WHEN THEY´RE 12.

11:49.239 --> 11:51.141
WHERE DO THE LIES STOP, MOM?

11:51.141 --> 11:54.484
RIGHT AFTER THIS.

11:54.484 --> 11:55.986
HERE.

11:55.986 --> 11:58.248
HE LEFT YOU
 THIS ST. CHRISTOPHER MEDALLION

11:58.248 --> 12:00.420
FOR PROTECTION OR SOMETHING.

12:00.420 --> 12:01.752
GET OUT!

12:01.752 --> 12:03.153
GEORGE!

12:03.153 --> 12:05.295
NO! THERE´S A GAS STATION
 ABOUT A MILE BACK.

12:05.295 --> 12:06.897
YOU CAN WALK.
 GET OUT!

12:06.897 --> 12:08.098
GEORGE, YOU CAN´T DO THIS.

12:08.098 --> 12:09.760
THERE´S BEEN TOO MANY LIES.

12:09.760 --> 12:12.232
I´M CONFUSED ENOUGH ABOUT MY
 FATHER, AND NOW YOU DO THIS.

12:12.232 --> 12:14.504
NO, I MEAN
 I TOOK OUT THE CAR KEYS

12:14.504 --> 12:17.167
WHILE YOU WERE WALKING
 MR. NEEDLES.

12:17.167 --> 12:18.809
YOU REALLY CAN´T DO THIS!

12:20.340 --> 12:22.272
GOT A SPARE ABOVE THE VISOR.

12:23.774 --> 12:25.946
GEORGE,
 I´M ALL FOR DITCHING HER,

12:25.946 --> 12:28.779
BUT LET´S NOT DO IT
 WITH MAX IN THE CAR.

12:28.779 --> 12:31.021
GET IN!

12:31.021 --> 12:32.783
YOU KNOW WHAT?
 FORGET IT!

12:32.783 --> 12:35.225
I CAN HITCH IT.
 I´LL SHOW SOME LEG.

12:35.225 --> 12:38.188
I´VE SEEN YOUR LEGS.
 YOU´LL DIE OUT HERE.

12:38.188 --> 12:39.329
GET IN!

12:54.204 --> 12:56.406
LOPEZ CONSTRUCTION.
 THAT´S IT.

12:58.348 --> 13:00.851
DO YOU HAVE ANYTHING TO SAY?

13:00.851 --> 13:01.481
NOPE.

13:01.481 --> 13:03.183
ANY ADVICE?

13:03.183 --> 13:05.916
I DON´T KNOW HOW YOU´RE GONNA
 FEEL WHEN YOU SEE YOUR DAD.

13:05.916 --> 13:09.489
BUT YOU´LL KNOW, AND YOU´LL SAY
 WHAT YOU NEED TO SAY.

13:09.489 --> 13:13.323
AND THEN ON THE WAY BACK, I CAN
 TELL YOU WHAT YOU DID WRONG.

13:13.323 --> 13:16.096
HEY, WHAT ARE SITTING HERE
 YAPPING ABOUT?

13:16.096 --> 13:16.967
WE´RE ALL GOING IN.

13:16.967 --> 13:18.428
NO!

13:18.428 --> 13:21.071
I´M GOING IN. WE´RE NOT EVEN
 SURE HE´S IN THERE.

13:21.071 --> 13:22.572
I´LL COME BACK AND GET YOU.

13:22.572 --> 13:23.573
WAIT, DAD...

13:23.573 --> 13:24.835
YEAH?

13:24.835 --> 13:25.906
PICK A COLOR.

13:27.237 --> 13:28.839
THIS IS TOTALLY DIFFERENT.

13:28.839 --> 13:30.210
YOU WANT TO BE PART
 OF MY DECISION?

13:30.210 --> 13:31.982
YEAH.

13:31.982 --> 13:34.084
OKAY. RED.

13:34.084 --> 13:36.516
R-E-D. NOW PICK A NUMBER.

13:36.516 --> 13:38.949
321.

13:38.949 --> 13:43.894
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8...

13:49.059 --> 13:50.600
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

13:50.600 --> 13:52.332
YEAH?

13:57.137 --> 14:00.070
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

14:00.070 --> 14:02.042
MANNY LOPEZ?

14:02.042 --> 14:03.273
YEAH.

14:05.045 --> 14:06.877
DO YOU KNOW WHO I AM?

14:06.877 --> 14:09.149
YOU FROM THE CITY?

14:09.149 --> 14:10.580
NO.

14:10.580 --> 14:13.283
UNION REP?

14:15.085 --> 14:16.887
I´M GEORGE LOPEZ.

14:18.628 --> 14:19.930
GEORGE.

14:19.930 --> 14:23.093
I WAS EXPECTING
 A CALL, BUT...

14:23.093 --> 14:25.395
THIS IS EVEN BETTER.

14:25.395 --> 14:27.537
I THOUGHT WE SHOULD TALK
 IN PERSON.

14:27.537 --> 14:31.141
GOOD, GOOD, GOOD.
 SIT DOWN, SIT DOWN.

14:31.141 --> 14:33.873
HOW´S YOUR MOTHER?

14:33.873 --> 14:35.145
THE SAME.

14:35.145 --> 14:38.008
OH, THAT´S TOO BAD.

14:38.008 --> 14:39.509
MY GOD.

14:39.509 --> 14:41.451
LOOK AT YOU.

14:44.454 --> 14:46.356
IN MY HEAD, YOU´RE ALWAYS 2.

14:46.356 --> 14:50.991
YOU AND YOUR FAMILY
 AROUND THE POOL.

14:50.991 --> 14:53.193
IT´S A GREAT PICTURE.

14:53.193 --> 14:55.065
WELL, IF YOU´RE GONNA BE
 AROUND FOR A WHILE,

14:55.065 --> 14:56.466
WHY DON´T YOU COME
 HAVE A SWIM?

15:00.670 --> 15:03.433
YOU KNOW, MAN, I CAN´T TAKE
 THIS CHECK FROM YOU.

15:03.433 --> 15:06.036
BENNY CALLED AND TOLD MY WIFE
 YOU NEEDED THE MONEY.

15:06.036 --> 15:08.008
WELL, SHE HAD NO RIGHT
 TO DO THAT.

15:08.008 --> 15:10.440
GEORGE, COME ON. TAKE THE CHECK.
 WE´RE FAMILY.

15:10.440 --> 15:12.242
YEAH?

15:17.917 --> 15:20.250
WHY DID YOU LEAVE?

15:20.250 --> 15:22.052
LOOK, THE PAST IS THE PAST.

15:22.052 --> 15:24.154
WHAT´S IMPORTANT
 IS I CAN HELP YOU NOW.

15:24.154 --> 15:26.196
I DON´T NEED YOUR HELP NOW.

15:26.196 --> 15:27.497
I NEEDED A FATHER.

15:27.497 --> 15:30.700
I MEAN, HOW COULD YOU LEAVE
 A FAMILY?

15:30.700 --> 15:32.932
YOU HAD A RESPONSIBILITY.

15:32.932 --> 15:34.934
I WASN´T GETTING ALONG
 WITH YOUR MOM.

15:34.934 --> 15:36.336
IT WASN´T MUCH OF A LIFE.

15:36.336 --> 15:39.209
BUT THINGS HAVE TURNED OUT
 FOR THE BEST.

15:39.209 --> 15:41.111
YOU CAME OUT OKAY.

15:41.111 --> 15:43.213
AND LOOK HOW WELL I´VE DONE
 FOR MYSELF.

15:43.213 --> 15:45.175
YOU THINK YOU´RE A SUCCESS?

15:45.175 --> 15:48.078
I DON´T CARE HOW MANY
 CHECKS YOU WRITE AND HOW
 BIG YOUR COMPANY IS.

15:48.078 --> 15:49.079
YOU´RE A FAILURE.

15:49.079 --> 15:50.520
AND YOU CAN´T BUY ME.

15:52.222 --> 15:55.355
HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT?
 YOU GOT THIS COCKINESS FROM ME.

15:55.355 --> 15:56.987
MAN, I DIDN´T GET ANYTHING
 FROM YOU

15:56.987 --> 15:58.688
BUT A LETTER FULL OF EXCUSES.

15:58.688 --> 16:00.690
EVEN WITHOUT A FATHER, I´M MORE
 OF A MAN THAN YOU´LL EVER BE.

16:00.690 --> 16:03.293
THAT´S ENOUGH!

16:03.293 --> 16:06.036
YOU LEFT A WOMAN SITTING IN
 THE LIVING ROOM WITH A KID
 AND NO WAY TO MAKE ENDS MEET!

16:06.036 --> 16:07.367
YOU TURNED YOUR BACK ON US!

16:07.367 --> 16:09.069
ARE YOU DONE?!
 NO, I´M NOT DONE!

16:09.069 --> 16:15.675
THE ONLY MISTAKE I´VE MADE

16:15.675 --> 16:17.347
THAT´S FOR MY MOTHER!

16:18.978 --> 16:22.552
NOW I´M DONE.

16:22.552 --> 16:26.256
297, 298...

16:26.256 --> 16:29.119
SEATBELTS ON! SEATBELTS ON!
 GO, GO, GO, GO!

16:29.119 --> 16:31.421
HE WASN´T THERE!

16:37.397 --> 16:39.529
STILL THINKING
 ABOUT YOUR DAD?

16:39.529 --> 16:42.532
ALL MY LIFE I WANTED TO SEE HIM
 WITH MY OWN EYES.

16:42.532 --> 16:44.774
IT WAS LIKE
 LOOKING AT A STRANGER.

16:44.774 --> 16:46.506
I´M SORRY.

16:46.506 --> 16:49.579
THERE´S JUST ONE THING I WISHED
 I WOULD HAVE ASKED HIM.

16:49.579 --> 16:50.740
WHAT´S THAT?

16:50.740 --> 16:52.542
WHEN DID HE START
 GOING BALD?

16:52.542 --> 16:54.484
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

16:54.484 --> 16:57.317
HOPE WE´RE STILL LAUGHING
 WHEN WE´RE BANKRUPT.

16:57.317 --> 17:01.591
DAD! CAN YOU HELP ME?
 I CAN´T GET THIS KNOT OUT.

17:01.591 --> 17:03.723
SURE, SON.

17:03.723 --> 17:06.796
I´M SORRY YOU DIDN´T GET
 ANOTHER GRANDPA LIKE YOU WANTED.

17:06.796 --> 17:08.198
THAT´S OKAY.

17:08.198 --> 17:10.329
BUT YOU GOT A DAD
 WHO LOVES YOU.

17:10.329 --> 17:13.803
AND NO MATTER WHAT,
 I´M ALWAYS GONNA BE -- [GRUNTS]

17:13.803 --> 17:16.306
ANGIE,
 HELP YOUR SON WITH THIS!

17:16.306 --> 17:18.568
FIND SOMETHING ELSE SO I CAN BE
 THERE FOR YOU, LIKE A BALL.

17:18.568 --> 17:19.539
OKAY.

17:22.712 --> 17:24.674
[ GASPS ] WOW!

17:24.674 --> 17:26.576
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

17:29.449 --> 17:31.581
DADDY!
 WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

17:31.581 --> 17:33.253
I´M HERE TO HELP.

17:33.253 --> 17:35.685
IF THAT MEANS I HAVE TO FIGHT
 WITH YOUR HUSBAND,

17:35.685 --> 17:37.687
SO BE IT.

17:37.687 --> 17:40.390
ANGIE, DID YOU ASK YOUR FATHER
 TO FLY OUT HERE?

17:40.390 --> 17:41.331
NO.

17:41.331 --> 17:42.632
SHE DIDN´T HAVE TO.

17:42.632 --> 17:46.596
A FATHER KNOWS WHEN HIS DAUGHTER
 IS IN TROUBLE.

17:46.596 --> 17:50.170
ESPECIALLY WHEN THE DAUGHTER
 CALLS THE MOTHER...

17:50.170 --> 17:52.602
TWO TIMES A DAY...

17:52.602 --> 17:55.375
AND THE MOTHER WON´T LET
 THE FATHER SLEEP.

17:55.375 --> 17:57.307
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

17:57.307 --> 17:58.748
WHAT DO YOU WANT, VIC?

17:58.748 --> 18:03.483
I WANT YOU TO TAKE A CHECK
 FOR $17,000 FROM ME.

18:05.315 --> 18:07.187
NOW LET´S FIGHT.

18:07.187 --> 18:11.221
OH, I´VE BEEN WAITING
 TO KICK YOUR BUTT FOR 16
 YEARS.

18:11.221 --> 18:14.524
I WILL BE CALLING YOU "FIDEL"
 AS I WHIP YOU.

18:18.668 --> 18:20.700
IS THIS SOME KIND
 OF HAND OUT?

18:20.700 --> 18:23.503
NO. IT´S A LOAN.

18:29.879 --> 18:31.381
OKAY.

18:32.382 --> 18:33.783
BUT I´M PAYING YOU INTEREST.

18:33.783 --> 18:36.716
I DON´T WANT INTEREST.

18:36.716 --> 18:38.288
THEN WE CAN FIGHT OVER THAT.

18:38.288 --> 18:41.251
AND I WILL BE CALLING YOU
 "BENNY" AS I WHIP YOU.

18:41.251 --> 18:45.325
OKAY, OKAY. THANK YOU, POP.
 THANK YOU.

18:45.325 --> 18:47.757
ONE CONDITION --

18:47.757 --> 18:49.259
I DON´T EVER WANT
 TO HEAR YOU SAY

18:49.259 --> 18:51.231
I CAN´T TAKE CARE
 OF MY FAMILY.

18:51.231 --> 18:53.663
I WORKED TOO HARD
 TO GET YOUR RESPECT.

18:53.663 --> 18:55.805
GEORGE...

18:55.805 --> 18:59.439
A MAN WHO PUTS HIS FAMILY
 BEFORE HIS PRIDE...

18:59.439 --> 19:02.512
IS SOMEONE
 I´LL ALWAYS RESPECT.

19:05.175 --> 19:07.277
THANKS, DAD.

19:07.277 --> 19:09.549
OH. NOW I´M YOUR DADDY!

19:10.820 --> 19:12.822
I SUPPOSE YOU WANT ME
 TO CHANGE YOUR DIAPIE.

19:12.822 --> 19:14.184
MAN!

19:14.184 --> 19:15.325
DON´T YOU
 WALK AWAY FROM ME, SON!

19:16.256 --> 19:18.328
YOUR FATHER IS TALKING TO YOU!

19:23.233 --> 19:24.564
ALL RIGHT, MOM.

19:24.564 --> 19:26.796
WE´RE ALL ALONE.
 LET´S CLEAR THE AIR.

19:26.796 --> 19:30.470
ARE THERE ANY MORE LIES
 I SHOULD KNOW ABOUT?

19:31.801 --> 19:32.842
YES.

19:33.543 --> 19:34.704
WHAT?

19:34.704 --> 19:37.847
WELL, THERE´S
 A BUNCH OF THINGS.

19:37.847 --> 19:40.310
BUT I´M GONNA SPACE THEM OUT

19:40.310 --> 19:43.653
SO I WON´T LOOK LIKE
 SUCH A BAD PERSON.

19:46.356 --> 19:48.758
I TOLD MANNY
 I HIT HIM FOR YOU.

19:48.758 --> 19:51.821
REALLY?

19:51.821 --> 19:54.924
THAT IS THE FIRST GIFT
 YOU EVER GAVE ME

19:54.924 --> 19:56.626
THAT I ACTUALLY WANTED!

19:57.897 --> 19:59.329
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

19:59.329 --> 20:03.373
I HIT HIM ONCE,
 AND HE WENT DOWN.

20:03.373 --> 20:07.337
PAINT A PICTURE FOR ME.

20:07.337 --> 20:12.211
THERE WAS BLOOD
 IN THE CORNER OF HIS MOUTH.

20:12.211 --> 20:15.685
[ Crying ] OH, GEORGE!

20:15.685 --> 20:17.747
[ SOBBING ]
